e class="article__info"><div class="article__info__left"><div class="article__info__author-container"> <a class="wide-title" href="https://news.bitcoin.com/category/economics/" title="Economics">Economics</a><p class="article__info__author"> by <a href="https://news.bitcoin.com/author/jamieredman/"><strong>Jamie Redman</strong></a></p></div></div><div class="article__info__right"> <time class="article__info__date"> Mar 4, 2020 </time><ul class="article__info__stats"><li> <span class="article__info__stats__icon hidden article__info__stats__icon--eye"></span> <span class="pvc-post-374366-current"></span></li><li class="comments_count hidden_counter"> <span class="article__info__stats__icon article__info__stats__icon--comment"></span> <span class="disqus-comment-count"></span></li></ul><div class="article__info__share-container"> <a class="article__info__share article__info__share--fb" href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.bitcoin.com%2Fcoronavirus-fed-interest-stocks-gold-bitcoin%2F " onclick="window.open(this.href, 'mywin','left=50,top=50,width=600,height=350,toolbar=0'); return false;"></a> <a class="article__info__share article__info__share--twitter" href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Coronavirus+Prompts+Fed+to+Slash+Interest+Rate+-+Stocks+Slide%2C+Gold+Spikes%2C+Bitcoin+Uncertainty&url=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.bitcoin.com%2Fcoronavirus-fed-interest-stocks-gold-bitcoin%2F&via=BTCTN"></a> <a class="article__info__share article__info__share--reddit" href="https://www.reddit.com/submit?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.bitcoin.com%2Fcoronavirus-fed-interest-stocks-gold-bitcoin%2F" target="_blank"></a> <a class="article__info__share article__info__share--linkedin" href="https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.bitcoin.com%2Fcoronavirus-fed-interest-stocks-gold-bitcoin%2F&title=Coronavirus+Prompts+Fed+to+Slash+Interest+Rate+-+Stocks+Slide%2C+Gold+Spikes%2C+Bitcoin+Uncertainty&summary=&source=" target="_blank"></a></div></div></aside><article class="article__body"><header class="article__header"><h1 class="article__header__heading" itemprop="headline"> Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty</h1></header><div class="featured_image_container"> <img width="1069" height="720" src="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash.jpg" class="story__img article__poster" alt="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, and Bitcoin Uncertainty" srcset="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash.jpg 1520w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash-300x202.jpg 300w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash-1024x690.jpg 1024w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash-768x517.jpg 768w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash-696x469.jpg 696w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash-1392x938.jpg 1392w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash-1068x719.jpg 1068w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash-623x420.jpg 623w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash-190x128.jpg 190w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash-380x256.jpg 380w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/fedslash-760x512.jpg 760w" sizes="(max-width: 1069px) 100vw, 1069px" /></div><div class="td-a-rec td-a-rec-id-content_top  "><a data-bid="1" href="https://news.bitcoin.com/linkout/398623" rel="nofollow" target="_blank"><!--noptimize--><img width="728" height="180" src='https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/lottery_major_728x180_bch.jpg' alt=''  /><!--/noptimize--></a></div><p><strong>The U.S. Federal Reserve slashed interest rates by 50 bps on Tuesday citing concerns about the coronavirus outbreak against the bleak economy. The last time the central bank slashed rates by leveraging an &ldquo;emergency rate shift&rdquo; by half a percentage point was after Lehman Brothers filed for bankruptcy in 2008. The announcement didn&rsquo;t have a favorable effect on the stock market and the Dow shed close to 800 points after Fed Chairman Jerome Powell announced the cut.</strong></p><p><em><strong>Also Read: </strong></em><a href="https://news.bitcoin.com/this-is-how-much-btc-you-need/"><em><strong>This Is How Much BTC You Need to Enter Bitcoin&rsquo;s Elite 1% Club</strong></em></a></p><h2 style="text-align: center;">50 bps: The Federal Reserve&rsquo;s First Emergency Rate Cut Since 2008</h2><p>It&rsquo;s safe to say that global markets have been shaken by the coronavirus crisis and governments and central banks worldwide are reacting. Last week U.S. stock markets were extremely bloody and assets like precious metals and cryptocurrencies took a hit too. On Monday the Dow Industrial Jones saw a 1,200-point advance as it seemed like a recovery was on the cards.</p><figure id="attachment_374463" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-374463" style="width: 616px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img class="wp-image-374463" title="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" src="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/dowjones44.jpg" alt="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" width="616" height="329" srcset="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/dowjones44.jpg 1450w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/dowjones44-300x160.jpg 300w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/dowjones44-1024x547.jpg 1024w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/dowjones44-768x410.jpg 768w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/dowjones44-696x372.jpg 696w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/dowjones44-1392x744.jpg 1392w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/dowjones44-1068x571.jpg 1068w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/dowjones44-786x420.jpg 786w" sizes="(max-width: 616px) 100vw, 616px"><figcaption id="caption-attachment-374463" class="wp-caption-text">After the Fed announced slashing the interest rate, the top three indices dropped like a rock. The Dow Jones Industrial Average saw close to 800 points shed almost erasing the 1,200 points it gained on Monday.</figcaption></figure><p>However, on Tuesday as coronavirus fears continued to extend across the globe, the U.S. Federal Reserve <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/03/economy/federal-reserve-rate-cut/index.html">cut interest rates by 50 bps</a> and explained it was due to the coronavirus crisis and the overall &ldquo;outlook&rdquo; of the economy. Almost immediately after the Fed&rsquo;s announcement, all three major stock indices dropped significantly percentage-wise and the Dow lost close to 800 points.</p><p>&ldquo;We saw the risk to the outlook to the economy and chose to act,&rdquo; Powell told reporters on Tuesday. &ldquo;I don&rsquo;t think anybody knows how long it will be,&rdquo; he added. &ldquo;I know the US economy is strong and we&rsquo;ll get to the other side of this and return to solid growth and a solid labor market as well.&rdquo;</p><figure id="attachment_374456" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-374456" style="width: 1450px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img class="wp-image-374456 size-full" title="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" src="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/powell.jpg" alt="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" width="1450" height="600" srcset="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/powell.jpg 1450w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/powell-300x124.jpg 300w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/powell-1024x424.jpg 1024w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/powell-768x318.jpg 768w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/powell-696x288.jpg 696w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/powell-1392x576.jpg 1392w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/powell-1068x442.jpg 1068w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/powell-1015x420.jpg 1015w" sizes="(max-width: 1450px) 100vw, 1450px"><figcaption id="caption-attachment-374456" class="wp-caption-text">&ldquo;The magnitude and persistence of the overall effect on the U.S. economy remain highly uncertain and the situation remains a fluid one,&rdquo; Powell said on Tuesday. &ldquo;Against this background, the committee judged that the risks to the U.S. outlook have changed materially. In response, we have eased the stance of monetary policy to provide some more support to the economy.&rdquo;</figcaption></figure><h2 style="text-align: center;">Lehman Brothers Crash, 9/11, and &lsquo;Undermined Confidence&rsquo;</h2><p>Since September 2019, the Fed has been feeding private banks with <a href="https://news.bitcoin.com/federal-reserve-considers-creating-a-separate-entity-for-cash-injections/">billions</a> in <a href="https://news.bitcoin.com/fed-officials-ponder-funding-hedge-funds-and-private-brokers-directly/">overnight repos</a> and it has cut rates three times already but not nearly as much as Tuesday. In fact, the last time the Fed cut rates by half a percentage point was during the 2008 economic crisis. One month before the &ldquo;emergency rate shift&rdquo; on September 15, 2008, the U.S. saw the largest bankruptcy in the country&rsquo;s history. Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc. filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy and the Fed decided to take action. Roughly three weeks later on October 8, 2008, the Fed used an emergency rate shift and cut rates by 50 basis points (bps) to 1.5%. &ldquo;The Committee took this action in light of evidence pointing to a weakening of economic activity and a reduction in inflationary pressures,&rdquo; the Federal Open Market Committee explained at the time.</p><p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-374466 size-full" title="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" src="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/lehman.jpg" alt="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" width="1800" height="1000" srcset="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/lehman.jpg 1800w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/lehman-300x167.jpg 300w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/lehman-1024x569.jpg 1024w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/lehman-768x427.jpg 768w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/lehman-1536x853.jpg 1536w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/lehman-696x387.jpg 696w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/lehman-1392x773.jpg 1392w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/lehman-1068x593.jpg 1068w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/lehman-756x420.jpg 756w" sizes="(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px"></p><p>Of course, the Fed did more than just that as they opened the floodgates of quantitative easing and stimulated private banks while the taxpayers had to foot the bill. 2008 saw <a href="https://www.thebalance.com/what-was-the-bank-bailout-bill-3305675">massive bank bailouts</a> and the Fed ultimately slashed the interest rate as low as 0.25%. Prior to the Lehman Brothers collapse, the Fed cut rates on January 22, 2008 by 75 bps and 50 bps in August 2007.</p><figure id="attachment_374484" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-374484" style="width: 740px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img class="wp-image-374484 size-full" title="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" src="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/106422373-158325481092620200303fedratecut.png" alt="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" width="740" height="416" srcset="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/106422373-158325481092620200303fedratecut.png 740w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/106422373-158325481092620200303fedratecut-300x169.png 300w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/106422373-158325481092620200303fedratecut-696x391.png 696w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px"><figcaption id="caption-attachment-374484" class="wp-caption-text">The history of emergency rate cuts or unscheduled decisions made by the U.S. central bank between 2005 up until now.</figcaption></figure><p>It was six years before the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emergency_Economic_Stabilization_Act_of_2008">2008 financial crisis</a> when the central bank slashed interest rates by 50 bps because of the 9/11 attacks. On September 17, 2001, a few days after the World Trade Center bombings, the Fed told the public the central bank would offer &ldquo;unusually large volumes of liquidity.&rdquo; The Fed&rsquo;s interest rate cut of 50 bps on Tuesday didn&rsquo;t have much of a favorable outcome on the New York Stock Exchange and Moody&rsquo;s Analytics Chief Economist Mark Zandi said it &ldquo;undermined confidence.&rdquo;</p><p>&ldquo;Cutting rates was the right policy choice, certainly the right thing to do, but doing it the way they did was a mistake,&rdquo; Zandi <a href="https://finance.yahoo.com/news/moodys-mark-zandi-calls-fed-rate-cut-timing-a-mistake-215058448.html?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly90LmNvL3pmT1RaNUJKWm4_YW1wPTE&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAGJn3fVmAeFp7UfgpVbJeCaF-yJIKO1FBR83OUafBi1OhAeN9_A37fcx6esG_RlvOb7M2Q7DDJN2BBEJhVLz6-QbgthFaOkjV-Mk-xgJyiBdAS708HuEU1P3Lh4HVgfnMxmxnTxz4jNMwbVYP9bS8p8Ew03bImKHekYDOjAkmFxM">explained</a> during an interview on Tuesday. &ldquo;Certainly we know that in hindsight,&rdquo; Zandi added. &ldquo;It didn&rsquo;t do what it was supposed to do and that was instill confidence. It, in fact, undermined confidence.&rdquo;</p><figure id="attachment_374469" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-374469" style="width: 1910px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img class="wp-image-374469 size-full" title="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" src="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/zandimoodys.jpg" alt="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" width="1910" height="1000" srcset="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/zandimoodys.jpg 1910w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/zandimoodys-300x157.jpg 300w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/zandimoodys-1024x536.jpg 1024w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/zandimoodys-768x402.jpg 768w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/zandimoodys-1536x804.jpg 1536w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/zandimoodys-696x364.jpg 696w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/zandimoodys-1392x729.jpg 1392w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/zandimoodys-1068x559.jpg 1068w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/zandimoodys-802x420.jpg 802w" sizes="(max-width: 1910px) 100vw, 1910px"><figcaption id="caption-attachment-374469" class="wp-caption-text">Mark Zandi is the chief economist of Moody&rsquo;s Analytics and the cofounder of Economy.com. Zandi explained that the Fed&rsquo;s rash decision to use an emergency rate cut didn&rsquo;t do what it was supposed to do and instead &ldquo;undermined confidence.&rdquo;</figcaption></figure><h2 style="text-align: center;">Gold Prices Soar</h2><p>Following the Federal Reserve&rsquo;s surprise interest rate cut on March 3, the price of the precious metal gold surged by $49 on Tuesday to $1,638 an ounce. Economist and gold bug Peter Schiff <a href="https://twitter.com/PeterSchiff/status/1234866279321919488">commented</a> on the Fed&rsquo;s move and said: &ldquo;Lower interest rates will do nothing to alter coronavirus related consumer behavior.&rdquo;</p><figure id="attachment_374472" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-374472" style="width: 770px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img class="wp-image-374472 size-full" title="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" src="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/gold_3d_b_o_usd.png" alt="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" width="770" height="410" srcset="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/gold_3d_b_o_usd.png 770w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/gold_3d_b_o_usd-300x160.png 300w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/gold_3d_b_o_usd-768x409.png 768w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/gold_3d_b_o_usd-696x371.png 696w" sizes="(max-width: 770px) 100vw, 770px"><figcaption id="caption-attachment-374472" class="wp-caption-text">After gold rallied following the 50 bps rate cut, gold bug Peter Schiff commented on cryptocurrency markets. &ldquo;If bitcoin can&rsquo;t rally with an emergency 50 basis point rate cut, plus all of the recent stock, bond, currency, and gold market volatility, under what circumstances will it rally? If Bitcoin won&rsquo;t go up, why own it? The answer to that question is &lsquo;sell,'&rdquo; <a href="https://twitter.com/PeterSchiff/status/1234947376722386945">Schiff tweeted on Tuesday.</a></figcaption></figure><p>&ldquo;The Fed&rsquo;s real concern was the reverse wealth effect lower stock prices would have on consumers and the economy. So the rate cut was not really about the coronavirus, but the stock market,&rdquo; Schiff added. Schiff also got some <a href="https://twitter.com/PeterSchiff/status/1235021574396231680">press</a> for predicting the current economic downturn and the 2008 financial crisis as well. While gold investors were pleased with the price of gold spiking after the Fed&rsquo;s announcement, cryptocurrency markets remained lackluster.</p><h2 style="text-align: center;">Cryptocurrencies and Coronavirus</h2><p><a href="https://markets.bitcoin.com">Crypto markets</a> did erase some gains on Tuesday but not nearly as close as the lift gold saw. While there are some people who believe a financial crisis would be good for <a class="lar-automated-link" href="https://markets.bitcoin.com/crypto/BTC" 311996  target="_blank">BTC</a> prices and the Fed&rsquo;s surprise cut was a cherry on top, other speculators believe the opposite. A <a href="https://twitter.com/cryptokanoon/status/1234702786144690176">survey</a> from the Twitter account <a href="https://twitter.com/cryptokanoon">Crypto Kanoon</a> says: &ldquo;There is a common narrative floating in the industry that coronavirus will take the stock market down hence it will lead to [a] bitcoin pump. Is there a correlation between [the] stock market and crypto?&rdquo; There are four answers that could be picked which include: &ldquo;stocks up and <a class="lar-automated-link" href="https://markets.bitcoin.com/crypto/BTC" 311996  target="_blank">BTC</a> down, stocks down and <a class="lar-automated-link" href="https://markets.bitcoin.com/crypto/BTC" 311996  target="_blank">BTC</a> up, it is random, and no correlation.&rdquo; With over 630 votes and more than 37.4%, the &ldquo;no correlation&rdquo; choice led the vote, but &ldquo;stocks down and <a class="lar-automated-link" href="https://markets.bitcoin.com/crypto/BTC" 311996  target="_blank">BTC</a> up&rdquo; followed slightly behind.</p><p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-374479 size-full" title="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" src="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/survey.jpg" alt="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" width="1450" height="550" srcset="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/survey.jpg 1450w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/survey-300x114.jpg 300w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/survey-1024x388.jpg 1024w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/survey-768x291.jpg 768w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/survey-696x264.jpg 696w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/survey-1392x528.jpg 1392w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/survey-1068x405.jpg 1068w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/survey-1107x420.jpg 1107w" sizes="(max-width: 1450px) 100vw, 1450px"></p><p>Blockchain angel investor Qiao Wang also discussed <a class="lar-automated-link" href="https://markets.bitcoin.com/crypto/BTC" 311996  target="_blank">BTC</a>&rsquo;s performance during a possible global recession. &ldquo;Sorry to put a pin in the bubble, but Bitcoin traded like an absolute sh**coin over [the] last couple of weeks,&rdquo; Wang <a href="https://twitter.com/qwqiao/status/1234956694154891265?s=21">tweeted</a>. &ldquo;If you are a crypto business or hold a large amount of crypto, you should probably start thinking about hedging against a mild global recession.&rdquo; Wang added:</p><blockquote><p><em><strong>Every short-term time frame I look at, be it 1 minute, hourly, or daily, Bitcoin looks depressingly correlated with [S&P 500]. I&rsquo;m not saying Bitcoin will necessarily get crushed by a mild recession, but you probably want to update your Bayesian probabilities.</strong></em></p></blockquote><figure id="attachment_374477" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-374477" style="width: 617px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img class="wp-image-374477" title="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" src="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/twobit.jpg" alt="Coronavirus Prompts Fed to Slash Interest Rate - Stocks Slide, Gold Spikes, Bitcoin Uncertainty" width="617" height="234" data-wp-editing="1" srcset="https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/twobit.jpg 1450w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/twobit-300x114.jpg 300w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/twobit-1024x388.jpg 1024w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/twobit-768x291.jpg 768w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/twobit-696x264.jpg 696w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/twobit-1392x528.jpg 1392w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/twobit-1068x405.jpg 1068w, https://news.bitcoin.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/twobit-1107x420.jpg 1107w" sizes="(max-width: 617px) 100vw, 617px"><figcaption id="caption-attachment-374477" class="wp-caption-text">Many old school bitcoiners are talking about the 50 bps rate cut and the economy on Twitter. &ldquo;I predict within 2-4 weeks we will see: record drops in economic markets, widespread quarantines in the U.S., all schools closed, over $100B in emergency government spending,&rdquo; <a href="https://twitter.com/brucefenton/status/1235176052865019905">said Chainstone Labs&rsquo; Bruce Fenton</a>. &ldquo;Possible nationalization of major industries and massive/unprecedented emergency measures,&rdquo; Fenton added.</figcaption></figure><p>Former Bitcoin Foundation director Bruce Fenton tweeted the situation as well. &ldquo;I&rsquo;d take some crypto off the table until this shakes out &mdash; Even Bitcoin will likely be hit by this &mdash; Long term fundamentals should be solid still,&rdquo; Fenton <a href="https://twitter.com/brucefenton/status/1234966651042439168">stressed</a>. &ldquo;The use case of limited supply money could be even more appealing. But a speculative and volatile asset will have a hard time,&rdquo; he added. Still, there are many people that believe <a href="https://markets.bitcoin.com/crypto/BTC">BTC</a> will perform as well as gold has in the last few days or fulfill everyone&rsquo;s uncorrelated asset theories.</p><p>&ldquo;[S&P 500] and Google Trends for &lsquo;coronavirus&rsquo; are almost mirror images of each other &ndash; SPX is nearly completely tied to coronavirus fear &mdash; r = -0.9,&rdquo; <a href="https://twitter.com/nsquaredcrypto/status/1235029780417761281">tweeted</a> Cane Island Alternative Advisors&rsquo; Timothy Peterson. &ldquo;Bitcoin is [the] least correlated (-> <a class="lar-automated-link" href="https://markets.bitcoin.com/crypto/BTC" 311996  target="_blank">BTC</a> doesn&rsquo;t care). Gold has been the best hedge: +0.6 correlation.&rdquo;</p><p><em><strong>What do you think about the Fed&rsquo;s interest rate cut and the effect on the stock exchange on Tuesday? What do you think about cryptocurrencies and how they will perform if the world is hit by a financial crisis? Let us know what you think about this subject in the comments section below.</strong></em></p><p><i><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This article is for informational purposes only. It is not an offer or solicitation of an offer to buy or sell, or a recommendation, endorsement, or sponsorship of any products, services, or companies. Bitcoin.com does not provide investment, tax, legal, or accounting advice. Neither the company nor the author is responsible, directly or indirectly, for any damage or loss caused or alleged to be caused by or in connection with the use of or reliance on any content, goods or services mentioned in this article.</i></p><hr><p><em>Images credits: Shutterstock, Twitter, Fair Use, Jerome Powell, Wiki Commons, goldprice.org, Google stocks, CNBC, and Pixabay. </em></p><hr><p><em>Did you know you can buy and sell <a class="lar-automated-link" href="https://markets.bitcoin.com/crypto/BCH" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BCH</a> privately using our noncustodial, peer-to-peer <a href="https://local.bitcoin.com/" t